  "sn1.48:1.1": "Linked Discourses 1",
  "sn1.48:2.1": "5 On Fire",
  "sn1.48:3.1": "48 Jeta’s Grove",
  "sn1.48:4.1": "“This is indeed that Jeta’s Grove,",
  "sn1.48:4.2": "frequented by the Saṅgha of seers,",
  "sn1.48:4.3": "where the King of Dhamma stayed:",
  "sn1.48:4.4": "it brings me joy!",
  "sn1.48:5.1": "Deeds, knowledge, and principle;",
  "sn1.48:5.2": "ethical conduct, an excellent livelihood;",
  "sn1.48:5.3": "by these are mortals purified,",
  "sn1.48:5.4": "not by clan or wealth.",
  "sn1.48:6.1": "That’s why an astute person,",
  "sn1.48:6.2": "seeing what’s good for themselves,",
  "sn1.48:6.3": "would examine the teaching rationally, ",
  "sn1.48:6.4": "and thus be purified in it.",
  "sn1.48:7.1": "Sāriputta has true wisdom,",
  "sn1.48:7.2": "ethics, and also peace.",
  "sn1.48:7.3": "Any mendicant who has gone beyond",
  "sn1.48:7.4": "can at most equal him.”"
}